1
00:00:06,046 --> 00:00:14,099
People, they like to see images that
reflect concepts that are in their hearts.

2
00:00:14,099 --> 00:00:17,852
[Heart Movies]

3
00:00:18,144 --> 00:00:23,757
We can see in the senses the subjective realm, 
and what we see, objective,

4
00:00:23,757 --> 00:00:29,172
and we’re forever trying to take what’s in the heart
out into the objective world.

5
00:00:29,172 --> 00:00:33,419
Actually, really we want to live
in the subjective world

6
00:00:33,419 --> 00:00:36,343
but we find ourselves
in the objective world,

7
00:00:36,343 --> 00:00:39,321
and that’s why people—
not only the Chinese, but everybody—

8
00:00:39,321 --> 00:00:44,669
they like to go to movies and
immerse themselves in an experience,

9
00:00:44,669 --> 00:00:48,715
it’s like you’re taken away
from the objective world for some time

10
00:00:48,715 --> 00:00:50,562
and you enter another world,

11
00:00:50,562 --> 00:00:58,425
and you’re voyeuristically envisioning
yourself through the characters there.

12
00:00:58,779 --> 00:01:04,055
That’s in a simple way;
that’s part of what people do through media,

13
00:01:04,055 --> 00:01:09,126
but there may be more profound
implications about that also.

